nodes.title: 🪄 Adetailer: Your Personal Face-Fixer
widgets_values:
Adetailer is like the friend who tells you when you’ve got something in your teeth but instead of embarrassing you, it **fixes** the problem for you. 🤗

📸 Step 1: Load up an image.

⚡ Step 2: Run 🙂

You can switch the Detector Model to bbox/hand for hand fixes. Just note: it masks the hand’s shape, so you’ll usually get the same finger count and pose as the original.

Tip 💡: Denoise strength matters here too. Tweak it!

nodes.title: Tweak Smart, Not Hard
widgets_values:
Look, you don’t need to study for a ComfyUI adetailer settings exam. 🥲

Just pay attention to the usual suspects especially denoise strength.

Everything else? Meh.
Unless you like overthinking sliders at 3AM. I don’t judge. 🤖✌️

💡 Pro Tip: The wildcard box is to force variety. For example, "blonde, brunette, redhead" one of those will be chosen randomly each time you hit "Run".

nodes.title: Expand Your Horizons (Literally) 🖼️
widgets_values:
You’ve got an image. It’s great. But what if you want… **more**? That’s where Outpainting comes in. ☝️

📸 Step 1: Load your image.

📏 Step 2: In the Expansion Size node, set how many pixels to expand.

⚡ Step 3: Generate

Boom your image just grew (after a long wait...). Like stretching pizza dough, but with pixels. 🍕 Is it kinda mushy? Drives Max up the wall. He is currently working on fixing that for v1.5 (or he better be 😑)

nodes.title: 🎨 Inpainting (Fix AI Nightmares)
widgets_values:
🎨 Inpainting is your "undo" button when AI decides to bless you with three-armed nightmares.

Step 1: Load an image.

Step 2: Right-click on the load image node. → Spend 5 minutes looking for "Open in Mask Editor." 🕵️

 Step 3: Realize how **annoying** that is.

Step 4: Mask cursed area.

Step 5: Generate and watch horrors vanish (maybe 😅).

Inpainting isn’t just for cursed limbs. You can use it to swap outfits, recolor hair, or rewrite reality one brushstroke at a time. 😎

Default Flux guidance for Flux Fill (not Flux Dev) is 30.
Still can poke it, prod it, and mess with it if your heart desires.

nodes.title: ⚡ Flux Advanced – RunPod Edition
widgets_values:
Welcome, **Noodler** 🍜. Yes, I'm still calling you that. 🙂

Max has us **wiggling** into the deep end with Adetailer, Inpainting, and Outpainting, aka the holy trinity of AI touch-ups with a side of Upscaling. 🍜

Level 1 was your cozy island 🏝️ Level 2 drops you into the jungle 🌴. Don’t worry, I’m still here, still noodling, still slightly unhinged. 😜

👇 Follow the noodle!

nodes.title: The Real Deal
widgets_values:
This is where the **real** upscaling magic lives.

Pick your upscale model. Don’t stress about being picky, Flux is gonna clean up the mess anyway.

Set your "Upscale By" amount in the upscale node based on the model you use (x2 or x4), and as always… keep an eye on denoise strength.
Higher = wild changes. Lower = keepin’ it close. 🎯

Ignore the other settings. Let 'em do their thing.
They’re background actors. You’re the director now. 🎬

Pro tip: The steps here are 10. Raise and compare if you like.

nodes.title: 😔 The Last Noodle?
widgets_values:
You're either dedicated or you've gotten lost clicking noodles and somehow ended up here. Either way, **respect**. 🫡

So, what's next? 🎯

Go forth and experiment wildly or brace yourself, because Level 3 is packing a lot. 

- Pulid, generate new images that keep a consistent face. 

- Redux, use the style of an image as a prompt. 

- Depth, strip the soul out of an image and prompt for what Flux should fill it with. 

- Canny, Depth's weird cousin that likes edge maps instead of depth maps. 

- And more 🙂

All you have to do is go back to RunPod and click "⚡ Unlock Mega Workflow".

nodes.title: A Word From Max
widgets_values:
Building this RunPod template took a huge amount of time. Figuring out Patreon authentication, RunPod quirks, adapting the workflow, and tons and tons of testing was no weekend project. 🥲

If you're subscribed to Power Users, you’re not just unlocking the Mega Flux Workflow. You’re literally making it possible for me to keep supporting RunPod users such as yourself. Like adding SDXL, Flux Kontext, and every future workflow I make. 

So I have to be real. If there's no support, I can't justify the time it takes to make these templates and port over future workflows. So if you sub just know: 

**You're the reason any of this is exists.**

nodes.title: Global Models (RunPod Edition)
widgets_values:
We’ve got an extra **(Down)Load UNET MXD** node here but  
Max renamed it to **Inpainting** and made it pink. 

It’ll fetch the model when you run **Inpainting or Outpainting** below.  

Wanna watch the download?  
Head to the **bottom panel**, second button in the **top right corner**. 📥

Thankfully this is **RunPod** and not Max’s potato WiFi. 🥲🥔
